inn1.comm: nice, length delivery outside off, Guptill leans forward and leaves
on the off stump this time, Guptill defends it back off the front foot
presses forward and defends the incoming delivery, slightly shorter, to the leg side
coming in with the angle again towards off stump, Guptill defends it back
straighter one on the middle stump now, another solid defence
shapes it in nicely towards off stump, didn't miss it by much as Guptill shouldered arms
pretty full outside off, Latham reaches out and drives it to Raza at cover
touch back of length this time around off, Latham defends off the back foot
leans into the ball outside off again, was slightly wide, and he pushed it into the covers
first runs and in such risky fashion! It was a shorter delivery outside off, Latham saw room and chased it without any footwork to just chip it over the slips
swings and misses! Leans forward to drive the fuller delivery and misses the outside edge
length delivery outside off again, he goes back to defend on the off side
bit of extra bounce for the incoming delivery, Guptill presses forward a bit and defends
brings it in nicely from outside off, Guptill leans towards the ball and leaves
wider outside the off stump now, this one shaped away and easier for Guptill to leave
too much room this time and no movement, Guptill goes back and punches that nicely just wide of Raza at cover for four!
this ones comes in with the angle towards middle and leg, on good length, and Guptill gets an inside edge to the leg side
slightly back of length, he targets the off stump and Guptill defends it to the off side
good bounce for the length delivery angling away from outside off, he lets it go
just back of length outside off, Latham defends it with soft hands square of the wicket and gets a good response from Guptill for the quick single
goes on the front foot a bit and defends solidly on the off side
errs down the leg side, shouts of 'catch it' as Guptill glances it fine and maybe got bat on it as it eluded the keeper's gloves by not much
more towards middle stump now, Guptill works it to midwicket

thick edge off the toe of the bat flies away and just clears mid-off. It was pitched up on the off side, Guptill looked to flick on the leg side but got a leading edge and it wasn't too far from mid-off
back of length towards off side, he defends it into the covers
presses forward a bit more on the off side and pushes it to cover point
length delivery well outside off with the angle, pushed into the covers again
run out chance, just misses the direct hit at bowler's end! LAtham shuffled well to the off side and ran for the risky single after defending with soft hands. Ervine didn't miss the stumps by much
length delivery comes in, he leans forward and defends
fuller on off and middle stump, solid defence from Guptill again
pretty wide outside off, it swings away further, Latham chases without footwork and misses
shapes it away outside off stump from just short of length, Latham lets it go
comes forward this time towards the length ball and leaves again
drives it uppishly into the covers, it was just wide of cover point and Raza puts in a hard chase, then slides at the boundary to keep it in
back of length and coming in, worked away towards square leg for one
short and wide outside off, he cuts off the back foot and gets two towards deep point
not much room for the short of length ball outside off, he defends with soft hands and runs in for one
towards the leg side, easily worked off the pads to square leg for one
shuffles towards off for the fullish delivery and clips it to mid-on
another quick single - he pushes the length delivery with a drive towards mid-off and set off quickly to make it in time
waits for the ball to come in from length outside off and defends on the off side
gets the inside half of the bat while working the ball to square leg for one
drives the full delivery away from the body towards point for one
leans forward on the off side and drives the length delivery into the covers
drives it in the air again, this one fell well short of mid-off
back of length now and shaping away slightly, he pushes the ball to cover point

mix up between the batsman, Latham is safe! Bit too full and it was driven firmly to mid-off who didn't collect it cleanly. He did pick the ball up and throw it to the keeper but Latham had turned back by then
towards middle stump now, worked off the back foot to midwicket
good, short ball coming in towards middle stump. Guptill got into position to pull or hook but left it at the last moment
direct hit this time, but it concedes an overthrow! Guptill defended the ball towards point and set off for the single, the fielder put in a dive, got the direct hit but it wasn't enough
angles the ball in towards middle and leg, Guptill stays back and defends solidly
accurate bowling continues, this one came in again and he defends on the leg side
looks to whip the ball from leg stump, and he gets enough on that to send it slightly fine on the leg side for four
room on the off side this time, it's full too and smashed down the ground with a lofted drive for a one-bounce four
fullish on the legs, clipped to deep midwicket for one
pretty full and flighted on the off stump, worked down to long-on for one
angling in towards Latham, it's worked into the covers
excellent fielding effort from Raza - he dives to his left and saves a possible four after Latham drove that firmly
comes down the track now to negate any possible turn and flicks it from middle and leg past midwicket for four

comes down again but he's given a catch this time, Nyumbu strikes in his first over! Latham charged down, unleashed a cross-bat heave against the turn and Cremer took a sharp catch to his left at midwicket. Umpires check for a no ball, it's fine. They check if the catch is clean and if Cremer rubbed the ball on the ground when he landed, and that looks fine too
back of length outside the off stump, runs it down to third man for one
keeps his head down and blocks the ball on the off side
beats him outside off with some swing, it was just short of length and he poked and missed
some more room, KW stays back and steers it to cover point
punches this back of length ball off the back foot just past cover, but cover point comes around and keeps it in
presses forward for the length ball and blocks the ball outside off
presses forward to the off side and blocks the length ball
slightly wider outside off, good flight again and he blocks it again
extravagant drive for the length delivery outside off, but can't clear cover
maybe some bat on that as it turned in from outside off, sharp turn as he looked to work it with the slip but it came out of the keeper's gloves
pushes the length delivery back to the bowler from length
this was flatter on leg stump, clipped off the back foot to midwicket for a quick single and they make it in time despite the direct hit
turns it towards leg stump from off, he goes back and helps it to midwicket for one
back of a length, just outside off, he sets up for a punch off the back foot, cannot time it
allows a length ball to come on and taps it behind square on the off side
punches off the back foot, this came slower off the surface, and he hit it in the air, but wide of the fielder, to mid off
takes it from the line of off and middle and tucks it wristily through midwicket
angled in a bit, good length, he takes a step forward and defends it back to the bowler
overpitched ball on middle and leg, he plays it out towards mid on
tossed up outside off stump, he moves across in the crease and blocks
bends early for a sweep, but drags it straight to the man at leg slip
was not sure whether to go forward or back as this spun in quickly, jabs it away square in the end
fetches a fuller one from outside off and hits it along the ground to long on
darted in to the pad, he leans forward and works it square
goes across and whips it behind square with the turn
punched hard down the track, bowler is in the way and parries it to his rigth
holds the line as it is pitched up outside off, he calmly opens the face as he leans forward and guides it behind square
shortish, width too outside off, and Williamson bashes a pull well in front of square
pushes a length ball solidly to wide mid on
quite wide, but he gets away with it, Williamson waits and cuts it fiercely, but Cremer manages to stop it at backward point
no width this time, and he gathers himself to play a defensive push to leg
shot! this was too full outside off, he takes a step forward, and lifts it so cleanly over extra cover
some bounce and turn, he was coming forward and adjusts to nudge it past leg slip
flatter, and he goes back to work it with the turn to deep backward square
pitched up outside off, pushed firmly to extra cover
was that an edge, he went for a big sweep, replays show it brushed the glove, that is a pretty difficult chance for the keeper, the ball changed direction after taking the glove
too full and straight and it's launched out of the park with a lofted on drive form KW, over the wide long-on boundary for six
back of length now around off, pushes it down to mid-on and says no
short and slightly wide outside off, KW goes back and steers it towards point
on length outside off, he leans forward and pushes to point
superb shot from KW - he stayed back for the short of length delivery outside off and lofted the ball over the in-field with a back foot punch for four
pivots on the back foot this time to work the ball to deep backward square leg for one
works the ball down the ground from off stump to long-on
small appeal for lbw as KW went back to work the ball to leg with the turn but it spun too much and trapped him just outside leg
comes down the track to take it on the full and flicks that beautifully in the air and in the gap for four between long-on and deep midwicket
goes on the back foot and defends the ball on the off side with a thick outside edge
stays back in the crease and helps the ball down the ground to long-on
sharp turn for Nyumbu again, it goes down the leg side past the batsman and they sneak in a bye too
flighted well outside off, KW comes down and drives it on the full to long-off
turns it away from outside off, cuts off the back foot to deep cover for one
fullish on the pads, flicked against the turn to deep midwicket and they come back for two
very poor delivery - it was a half-tracker outside off and turned away a lot, KW chased for some reason and got some bat on it
almost beats him as it's a straighter one, KW defends it just in time and it just misses the stumps
presses forward to block the ball around off but it has some flight and turns away beautifully to beat him
flatter on middle and leg, clipped off the pads to deep square leg
comes down for the wide delivery outside off, he takes it on the full and drives that between mid-on and deep midwicket, well in the gap for four
goes back in the crease and defends the ball back
turning in from outside off, he stays back again and punches the ball back
takes a step down and clips the ball to leg uppishly
waits for the ball to turn into him and pulls it to square leg
comes down the track, not aggressively, and blocks the ball back
flighted and full on the stumps, blocked back to the bowler
too short, it turn away too to give him room and he smashes that through the covers, helped by the cover fielder with a misfield
cuts the ball off the back foot towards point for one
comes down and gets a thick edge to leg side, but for one

the flight has worked, very well bowled from Cremer to draw Guptill forward with a defence. He pressed and prodded and the ball turned away to get the outside edge, to Masakadza's right for a sharp, low catch
flighted on the leg side, Munro looks to defends but lets it hit him on the pads
goes deep in the crease to work the ball to midwicket with the turn
bit too short, he tries to whip it to leg but takes it on the body
opens up and helps the ball to deep midwicket off the back foot for two
clips the ball off the pads towards deep fine leg now for one more
reverse-sweeps the shortish ball on the off side, gets an edge over the slip fielder and gets three
too short, it's turning in and he pulls it to deep midwicket for two more
flighted on the leg stump, flicked with the turn to the leg side in the gap for two
looked like a googly outside the off stump, it was flighted and he worked it behind square
too short outside off with some turn, pulled awkwardly to deep midwicket
goes on the back foot for the ball that's coming in, and defends it to leg
turning in again from around off, helped to midwicket
length delivery on middle stump now, he blocks it back
swats the ball that's turning in to square leg
goes down on a knee to sweep, but it's shortish and he pulls it to deep fine leg for two
short of length outside off, punched into the covers off the back foot
short ball again, he pulls it again, just wide of square leg for one more
flighted and full on middle and leg, blocked back to the bowler
presses forward this time defends the length ball back to Raza
flighted outside off, it's driven with the turn to deep cover
turning in from off stump, worked with the turn to leg slip
turning it into the batsman, helped away to deep backward square leg
he finds the gap for two more with a pull and brings up his fifty
turning away from outside off, steered to point off the back foot
shorter and wider, cuts it firmly to deep point for one
flattish on middle and leg, helped to backward square leg for one
worked off the back foot with the turn to deep midwicket for one
pushes the length delivery into the covers with a drive for one
blocks the length ball outside the off stump
almost stumped! The ball went under KW's bat as he came down and the keeper couldn't hold on to the ball to stump him. How much will this cost them?
flicks this one in the air, lucky again as it goes just over the midwicket fielder and all the way to the boundary
turning in from off stump, pulled powerfully to deep midwicket for one
full and drifting in towards middle, driven down to long-off for one

plays across the line and is beaten comprehensively, bowled'im! Some flight for the ball outside off, Munro hardly moved to get into position to play that, it turned in sharply and went through the massive gap between bat and ball to hit top of middle stump
full and flighted on middle, driven straight to cover
flighted one outside off, nicely tossed up, and he blocks it back
beats him outside off by pitching it a touch shorter, drawing him forward to poke, and the turn beats the bat
works the ball with the turn and off the back foot to deep midwicket
turning in from just short of length to leg, steered to square leg for one
length delivery on the pads, helped to backward square leg
full toss on the off stump, pushed down to long-on easily
sloppy keeping again as it turned down the leg side past the batsman, and he let it go through him for a bye. Strange that it wasn't called a wide
flighted and full outside off, driven down the ground to long-off
turning away from outside off, pushed to cover
goes back for the flatter one and gets his bat down just in time to defend it
too short, there's turn too and he smacks it to the square-leg boundary in the gap for four
tossed up on middle stump, pushed back to Cremer
goes deep in the crease and whips the ball against the turn past midwicket for one
outside leg on length and it's swept fine, just wide of leg slip, to the fine-leg boundary for four
on length outside off, he goes back to defend it to leg
shuffles across to off and paddles it with the turn, fine on the leg-side boundary in the gap. Panyangara puts in a dive but can't keep it in
chips it in the air towards midwicket, falls well short
fullish on off and it's driven down to long-on for one
too wide outside off and it's driven down to long-off this time
tries to cut the ball late from outside off but doesn't connect
brings this one in from outside off, he lets it go
turns the ball into the batsman, he blocks it back
turns it in a bit from well outside off, it's left alone
presses forward for the length delivery on off, and blocks
touch fuller on the middle stump, he blocks it with a straight bat
coming in with the angle, KW waits for it and blocks
too full on the middle stump and it's driven down to long-on for one
shuffles to off and gets an inside edge, responds well to KW's call for one
angling in slightly towards leg, he drives it down to long-on for one
pretty full outside off as he comes down, steered to cover point
presses forward to the off side and defends it to point
pitched up outside off, slammed to the covers and Cremer does well to stop it
well outside off and it's cut to deep cover for one
pretty wide outside off and beats him too with the turn, but it's a wide
closer to the off stump and he presses forward to block it
cuts the ball off the back foot to short third man
shorter and wider, it was there to be punished but he found cover
another poor delivery with width, he slams it off the back foot and finds cover again
bangs in a bouncer around off and it's called a wide
length delivery has some room and it's driven straight to cover point
gives him the charge with a hard-hands shot and gets an edge to the off side
too full and wide, KW goes down on a knee and slams it over the covers with an elegant inside-out drive for four
width outside the off stump and he cuts it late towards third man
slow offcutter from back of length outside off, he guides it to third man
closer to the off stump, he steers the ball off the front foot to point
outside off with turn and it's punched into the covers for one
flight and some turn on middle stump, blocked off the front foot
drives the fuller delivery down to long-off
looks for the reverse-sweep with the turn but is beaten
cuts this one off the back foot, straight to point
presses forward and blocks the ball to cover point
punches the short of length ball into the covers
back of length outside off now, runs it to third man for one
tucks the ball from middle and leg towards midwicket for one
makes room, gets a full delivery and slams it down the ground, over the long-off boundary for six
comes down a step and he leaves the slower bouncer
attempts a yorker and sends a wide down the leg side
short ball and it's pulled to fine leg for one
on length outside off, Elliott shuffles across and paddles it against the turn to the fine leg boundary for four
bit too short outside off, punched off the back foot to sweeper cover for one
full outside off, driven straight to cover
pretty full again outside off, driven down the ground to long-off
reverse-sweeps the turning ball behind square on the off side
pushes the length ball straight to cover but the fielder throws unnecessarily to concede and overthrow
flighted on middle stump, he presses forward and blocks
similar delivery with similar flight on middle stump, it's pushed back to the bowler
flatter and shorter on middle stump, he blocks it back
nice turn outside off for the flattish delivery, he gets behind it and blocks
tries to break the shackles with a pull but mistimes it to midwicket
takes a step down to work the ball against the spin to midwicket for one
wide delivery outside off, turns away too and it's slammed to deep point for one
appeal for run out on the second run! He made room for the ball that angled in and punched it through the covers in the gap, the throw was pretty accurate from the deep but he made it back in time
flatter and quicker on off stump, pushed to cover point for one
bit of turn for the length ball on off stump, he presses forward and defends on the off side for one
paddles the ball against the turn from outside off to fine leg
quicker one on middle stump, he closes the face of the bat to leg and gets a thick outside edge to off
flighted on the middle stump, driven nicely into the covers
googly from middle stump, he makes room and pushes the ball back
misfield in the deep and that's four! Elliott swept the ball hard against the turn to fine leg and a misfield there led to four runs
that's the third wicket for Cremer, Elliott gone too! He swept again, but the ball wasn't full and turned to get a leading top edge to balloon towards Chigumbura at short fine leg
turning in from middle stump, worked to square leg with the turn for one
straighter on off stump, KW goes back to work it to the leg side in the wide gap and Cremer himself goes after the ball. They come back in time for the second
towards the pads and it's worked to the leg side for one

he's fallen in the 90s again, what a stunning catch at long-on! KW came down and lofted the ball down the ground, Ervine ran to his left from long-on, caught the ball right at the boundary and was then going over so threw ball in, kept himself in the chase and jumped back in just in time to catch it again. He knows he's caught it cleanly. KW did come down the track on the off side but never got close to the ball
just short of length outside off, pushes to cover for one
nice amount of turn outside off, pushed off the back foot to cover
waits for the ball to turn in and then leaves it
slams the short ball after it turns in to deep midwicket for one
length delivery outside off, pushed off the front foot into the off side for one
flat on the off stump, worked off the back foot to leg for one. A direct hit would have had Ronchi in trouble
flighted on middle stump, pushed back to the bowler
turn this time outside off, he lets it go to the keeper
goes back for the short ball and pulls it straight to midwicket
cuts the ball turning away from him in the air and straight to point
tossed up outside off and it's swept to deep backward square leg for two
on the pads now and it's clipped behind square on the leg side for two more
turning outside off and it's pushed back to the bowler off the back foot
length delivery on leg stump now, defends it back now
on the off side now and it's pushed to cover for one
goes back for the ball to turn in and defends it back
outside leg on length, it's clipped to square leg
quicker one on the stumps, flicked to the leg side off the back foot
bowls this one on the pads again and Neesham fails to connect
goes back in the crease for the shorter delivery and helps it behind square on the leg side for two quick runs
flighted and slower on leg, pushed straight to midwicket
back of length outside off, punched off the back foot to deep cover
touch short of length outside off, he swats it straight to midwicket
touch wider outside off, he guides it late to short third man
full on off now, heaves the ball to leg for one
comes down the pitch and gets an inside edge onto his body
turning in from off, not giving any room, and he defends it back
flighted outside off now and he slams that through the covers with some power, all along the ground for four
length delivery outside off, defends on the off side with an inside edge for a quick signle
some room outside off and he cuts it to backward point
full now, there's width too and it's driven to deep cover for one
errs down the leg side for a wide now
on middle stump and it's chipped in the air towards deep midwicket for one
he's holed out to deep midwicket, Ronchi falls too! It was a short ball, he opened up and went on the back foot to pull it to Madziva at deep midwicket
shuffles to the off side and steers the low full toss to the leg side for one
back of length and cutting in, pushed off the back foot to point
tucks the ball to leg from outside off with a thickish edge. No ball for overstepping
clever slower bouncer that McCullum doesn't get any bat on, but it's called wide for height
makes room for the full delivery and drives it on the off side
beats him! There was some away movement after the ball pitched on leg stump and moved away from Neesham, he didn't connect and looked back in disbelief
drives the full delivery into the covers and they come back for the second, helped by the inaccurate throw
full on off and it's slammed down the ground past the bowler for a cracking four
full outside off, it's thumped over long-on with a free swing for a huge six
short of length outside off, pushed into the covers for one
takes a step down and clips the full toss to the leg side for one
stays back in the crease and cuts that short of length delivery firmly to deep point for one
pitched up on leg and Nathan has done a Baz! He went down on a knee and slog-swept that to the midwicket boundary for a big six
length delivery on the stumps, turned to the leg side between long-on and deep midwicket. Another no ball
full toss on the off side, it's slammed down the ground and reaches long-off after a bounce
flatter on the pads, it's clipped behind square on the leg side for one
almost in the block hole well outside off, steered to point for one
in the block hole now, he makes room and drives it down to long-off for one
full again on the off side, struck down firmly to long-off for one more
goes way across to the off side and paddle-scoops it fine before short fine leg runs to his left and stops it
targets the block hole on the off side and it's steered to point
full on the stumps, lofted down to long-off in the air for one
it's a yorker on the stumps and McCullum drills it down to long-on to come back for the second
full on the pads, drilled wide of long-on this time and Raza stops it with both hands
gets some room outside off and he whacks that in the air over the covers. Only one this time
shuffles way outside off to scoop that on the leg side and he gets an inside edge for one
drives the full delivery down the ground for one more
gets a thick edge as he flays at this one, it was well outside off with room, and sent it wide of third man for four

inn2.comm: starts off with a swinging wide down the leg side
bit of inswing again towards the batsman, he takes it on the pads in front of leg
touch shorter on middle and leg and it's clipped to square leg off the back foot
back of length and towards middle stump now, he looks to defend off the back foot
fuller on the stumps now and it's clipped towards midwicket for the first run off the bat
nips in from back of length after pitching on middle and cramps the batsman for room, his bat comes down just in time to tuck it to leg
short of length on leg now, he goes on his toes to defend and the ball lobs off his thigh pad
turning in from outside off, worked down to long-on for one
bit of room on the off side, he cuts off the back foot to short third man
length delivery on the stumps now, helped to midwicket
goes just wide of slip! Chibhabha waited for the ball to turn in from outside off and then cut it late tentatively, went just wide of slip, luckily for Chibhabha
pushes the ball off the back foot into the covers
turns it in towards middle and leg, worked to midwicket
straightens after pitching around leg stump, he's hit on the pad but it's missing for height and line
towards off stump now, he defends off the back foot into the covers
that's gone high, he played it too early and chipped it just over mid-on. It was in the air for a while, pushed at it and just checked his shot. Lucky again
looks to work the ball to leg side and gets a leg bye
goes across a bit and defends the straight ball to the leg side off the back foot
goes back again, this was going towards middle stump and he clips it to midwicket
turning in a bit from well outside off, pretty flat, and it's helped to midwicket
pushes the ball softly towards long-on but midwicket dives to his left and stops it
pitched up and Masakadza tonks that with a slog-sweep to the midwicket boundary for a massive massive six!
straighter and flatter one outside off, he defends off the back foot
flighted and low full toss outside off, drilled down to mid-off at the edge of the circle
flatter and turning to leg, helped to square leg
back of length and accurate line on off stump, he defends off the back foot
drives that length ball down firmly, but straight to mid-on
goes back in the crease and defends the short of length ball
bangs in the bouncer towards leg stump
pulls the back of length ball from leg stump but mistimes it to midwicket
another bouncer, this one angling across outside off and he lets it go
nicely bowled with the angle outside off, Masakadza looked to defend but didn't, left it alone
bouncer from McClenaghan over the batsman, that's too short and it's called wide
short of length on the leg side, worked away towards square leg for one
he's going on the back foot for every ball, tucked this one from off straight to midwicket
finally off the mark, but not in convincing fashion. He pulled it late and got it behind square for one
nicely angled outside the off stump from back of length, good bounce and he lets it go
crunched through the covers for four! There was room, there was length for Masakadza and he drilled it through the covers with a powerful drive along the ground
on the back foot and tucked past midwicket for one
stays on the back foot and defends the ball back from off stump
top edge for four right behind the keeper! It was short on middle, it was pulled a little late and the top edge flew high and right over the keeper for a one-bounce four
beaten this time outside off! Nicely angled away, Masakazda poked at it and missed
punched from outside off straight to short cover
angled in towards off stump, he defends it off the back foot
leans towards the ball this time and pushes it into the covers
cuts and misses! There was some room this time, touch short of length as he chased without any footwork and was beaten
bangs in another bouncer, called wide again for height
nicely whipped off the back foot from chest-height towards deep square leg
short of length outside off, pushed into the covers
fuller delivery with the angle outside off, he leaves this time
leans towards the ball this time and pushes it into the covers
short of length on the pads, tucked towards deep square leg for one
stays back and defends the ball into the covers
touch short of length outside off, punched to short cover
back of length again, that's what they are sticking to, and he defends it to backward point
angles it down the leg side past the batsman for a wide
punched through the off side for four! Short of length with room and he square-drove it between point and cover point for a cracking four
presses forward and defends the ball solidly on the off side
guides the ball late from outside off towards third man for one
not so full on the stumps but he's looking in good touch and drives it exquisitely down the ground with the full face of the bat past the bowler for four
solid defence back to the bowler off the back foot
short of length and angling in, he defends to leg off the back foot
bangs it in short again, this time just outside off and he defends it to cover
bit more room outside off, helps it to backward point
defends the ball just in time in front of the off stump
drives the fuller delivery down to mid-on
stays on the back foot and whips the ball to square leg
drives the full ball firmly back to the bowler, another dot ball for Chibhabha
good bounce outside off, Chibhabha looked to defend but the ball took off from just back of length
loud appeal for lbw as he's struck in front of leg, but it was going down with the angle
starts with one towards the leg side, they take a leg bye behind square on leg
unleashes a powerful cut off the back foot as he was given width but deep point cut it in for two
drives it firmly to mid-off for a quick single
tries a slow yorker and Masakadza defends it back
full and straight on the stumps, pushed to midwicket off the front foot
slower on the middle stump, flicked down to long-on for one
cuts the ball outside off and luckily gets an inside edge just past the keeper for a four on the leg side
solid defence off the back foot for the short of length ball
some room outside off, he helps it late to third man for one
angled towards the pads and it's deflected to the leg side for a single
punches the straight length delivery back to the bowler
full delivery well outside off and it's driven down to mid-off
short ball towards the stumps and it's pulled wide of deep midwicket for two, that's the 50 partnership
defends the ball with soft hands towards short third man for a quick single
that's full, that's gone all the way! He packed a lot of power into that lofted drive and smashed it straight down the ground for six
stays back and defends the ball to leg this time
length delivery on the stumps and it's pushed down with a nice straight drive towards long-on. Masakadza was sent back for the second
there's room on the off side and he slams it wide of cover in the gap, two more
starts with a horrible half tracker and Masakadza dispatches it to the midwicket boundary for a four in the gap. Great start to the over for Zim
defends the length ball back to Sodhi off the front foot
short of length on off and turning away, pulled to long-on for one
beaten with the quicker one that turned a bit outside off and went over the bat
leans forward this time and pushes the ball to point
takes a small step down and pushes the ball to long-on for one
it turns towards leg and Chibhabha helps it to square leg
sharp turn into the batsman and he pushes to square leg again
presses forward and blocks the ball to the off side
goes back and makes room to only punch the ball to cover
another one off the back foot, it was in the air but just wide of cover
wants to sweep the ball from well outside off but takes it on the pad
some flight and turn outside off and he drives that firmly into the covers with the turn, beating mid-off as well for his first four
goes on the back foot to let it turn and steers to deep cover for one
cuts the ball nicely off the back foot to deep point for one
flight and drift on middle stump, low full toss is steered to midwicket
punches the ball with the turn on the off side, it's a chase for the fielder in the deep at deep cover, he puts in the dive and gets a hand to it but can't keep it in
turning in from outside off, he reaches out and sweeps that behind square in the air for a four!
fullish on off stump, driven down to long-on and he brings up his fifty, off 57 balls
turning in towards the pads, worked to deep midwicket for one
short of length outside off, punched towards cover for one
presses forward for the turning ball and defends it to leg side
a flat leg break on middle and off, played back to the bowler
driven on the front foot towards mid off
tossed up on off stump, he mis-times the drive towards the off side, the bowler fields
driven on the front foot through the covers this time, got to the pitch of that nicely
pitches on off and spins away, the length isn't full so the batsman hangs back and dabs towards point
played back to the bowler on the front foot
bowled flat and straight, played from the crease on the leg side
steps forward and towards the off side to drive a full ball through midwicket
bowled quick on off and middle, the batsman goes back and plays on the leg side
defended on the off side
driven on the front foot to coverd
dabbed off the back foot towards point
firmly drives the ball down to mid-off
short ball angling in, pulls it off the back foot to fine leg for one

double chance for Masakadza to get out - cuts it fiercely just wide of a diving point fielder first, survives that. Then dangerously comes back for the second and the throw is accurate at the keeper's end, but Ronchi doesn't collect the ball properly. Masakadza survives again
pulls the short ball but mistimes it to midwicket
defends it solidly off the back foot back to the bowler
slightly slower on middle and leg, he defends with soft hands
horrible, short ball down leg for a wide
outside off now and it's pushed to cover
comes down the track and flicks the ball with the turn to midwicket
gets room outside off and drives that inside out over the in-field for a four
another wide down the leg side
comes down the pitch and pushes it back to KW
works the ball with the turn to midwicket
makes room on the back foot and punches it to deep cover
gone, off stump goes for a stroll! McClenaghan angled the ball in from just outside off stump, the ball just about held its line as Chibhabha played inside it and missed the ball completely
loud appeal first ball in front of off stump, turned down! It nipped in sharply from outside off and caught Ervine on the back foot but he was saved by the height
wider outside the off stump and he lets it go
shorter and wider outside the off stump, Ervine drops his hands

what a drive to open his account! It was pitched up outside off and he crunched that with a straight bat, just beating a diving mid-off. That should give him truck loads of confidence after the appeal on the first ball
is beaten outside off now as the ball nips in and goes past Ervine's inside edge
turning in towards middle and leg, pushed down to long-on for one
towards leg stump, it's clipped to midwicket for one
works the ball with the turn to deep midwicket for one more
drives the ball uppishly away from his body, went just wide of cover for one
oh my, he's given a straightforward catch to deep midwicket! It was a poor short ball, Masakadza went back to pull it, but handed it straight to Wheeler in the deep. He's absolutely gutted
fullish outside off, driven off the front foot straight to cover
errs down the leg side but it brushed the pad on the way
pushes the ball into the off side but gets an inside edge to the leg side
angles it in towards the stumps, no room at all and Ervine defends solidly
gets some room and punches that nicely just in the gap for four. Cover point got a hand to it with a dive to his left but couldn't stop it properly
offcutter into the batsman and towards the stumps at good pace, the bat comes down just in time
stays on the back foot and defends the ball from off stump to the leg side
comes down the track and drives the ball nicely to mid-off
uses his feet again and flicks the ball with the turn to leg
gets an inside edge off the back foot, just past the keeper for one
short ball turning in, pulled to fine leg for one
slower length delivery on the off stump, he blocks on the front foot
full on the pads now and it's driven down easily to long-on for one
comes down the track for a short of length ball and tucks the ball to midwicket with the turn
short and flat and turning away, Chigumbura couldn't get close to the ball to cut it properly
chipped straight to cover, another wicket given away! Tossed up outside off and Chiggi drove that for an easy catch to Guptill around shoulder height
outside the off stump and it's swept with the turn towards fine leg for one
tucks the ball with the turn towards midwicket
drives this fuller delivery straight down for a single this time
too much down leg and Ervine sweeps that full delivery nicely to the fine-leg boundary for four!
waits for it to turn outside off and pushes it wide of cover point for one
comes down to take it on the full and lofts is straight down the ground, does he clear the fielders? Yes he does, it's a six!
wants to pull the ball to leg but it turns away from him
too short now, Williams pulls it properly this time against the turn and beats the fielder in the deep for another boundary
works the ball with the turn behind square leg for one
pushes the full delivery from off to midwicket
Sodhi appeals loudly as it turned in just a bit to hit him in front of middle and leg, but was probably turning down leg
straighter one outside off on length, he pushes it to point
flatter on leg stump, swept powerfully to deep fine leg
beaten just outside off as he went back to push the ball to off but missed his outside edge
another short ball and it gets the right treatment, pulled away over midwicket or a big six!
pushes the straighter ball back to the bowler
works the fuller ball towards square leg
some room outside off, turns a bit too, and he cuts it in the gap behind square for two more
way outside off with some turn away from the batsman
drives the fuller ball down the ground to long-off for one
gets an inside edge as he closes the face of the bat, to the leg side for one
back of length on the off stump, he defends it off the back foot
angling in a bit and he works it towards deep midwicket for one
too short, why are they bowling so many of those! He stayed back and pulled that nicely to the midwicket boundary for a four!
right in the block hole on the stumps, Williams blocks it back
another short ball, pulled away with style to deep square leg now
defends the ball from outside off with soft hands towards the slip region for a quick single by the time Ronchi gets there and throws
length delivery on the off stump, tucked to midwicket off the front foot
pushes the ball in the air from off stump to long-on for one
pushes it back uppishly again, just wide of the bowler to long-on
tries to pull the short of length ball to leg, but gets an inside edge onto his body
length delivery outside the off stump, pushed off the front foot to cover point
full delivery outside off, driven to cover where a dive saves a run or two
full outside off, driven down straight to mid-off
full and angling in towards the pads, clipped straight to midwicket
back of length now, pulled off the back foot behind square on the leg side and he calls for two early and gets it
short ball angled in slightly, hooks and misses
outside off now, driven away into the covers but straight to the fielders

is he run out, depends if it's a direct hit or not, it goes up to the third umpire! Williams defended the back of length ball close to himself on the off side but Ervine was way out of the crease by the time Williams said no, wasn't a late call. Wheeler ran to the ball, picked it and turned around early for a direct hit too! He's gone despite the dive, big big wicket
leans towards the ball and pushes it to cover for one
short of length outside off, he defends it into the covers
fullish on the off stump, chipped in the air down the ground, falls well short of long-on for one
length delivery is pushed down the ground back to the bowler
back of length around off, no room, and he pushes it back again
turns on the back foot now and clips it to midwicket
he came down the track and was beaten by the length and turn, the ball took the flap of the pad and went just past the keeper for two leg byes
spinning into him and he tucks it to leg for one
leans towards the ball and pushes it into the covers
drives it nicely through the covers with the turn in the gap
pushes this ball off the back foot into the covers for a quick single
flighted outside leg, it's pushed straight to midwicket
length delivery on the off stump, worked down to mid-off
bit too short and he pulls that to deep midwicket for one
short of length and angling in, tucked towards deep backward square and they are determined to get back for the second. Williams does well to make it in time
fuller around off, pushed down to mid-off with a straight bat
coming in sharply from outside off, makes a bit of room and cuts to cover point
room on the off side, he swings his arms to find deep point
nicely flighted on the middle stump, it's full too, and driven down to long-on for one
pretty flat on off stump with a hint of turn, worked towards cover point

stunned silence at the ground as Raza holes out too! It was flighted outside off, Raza swung his arms and punched a lot of power into that lofted drive, but gave a simple catch to long-off, who was not even right at the boundary. Raza is stunned too!
full again outside off, driven to cover off the front foot
short ball with some turn, pulled and it's mistimed but just over midwicket safely
flighted full toss on leg, flicked nicely to the leg side for one
some room outside the off stump, he cuts off the back foot to deep cover
turning in from off stump, he goes across and scoops it over the vacant leg-slip region for two
stunning catch from McCullum! Chakabva pushed the short of length ball back, but uppishly, and McCullum leapt to his right, rather flew and grabbed it with both hands
turning in from off and it's pushed down back to the bowler
sharper turn into the batsman and it's somehow helped towards short fine leg for one
goes for an extravagant sweep from well outside off, but it turns away even more
full outside the off stump, driven through the covers for one
full and turning in, chipped down to long-on for one more
flatter and shorter on the stumps with some turn, flicked to midwicket
touch wider outside off, pushed into the covers off the back foot
big swing outside off, but it turns away from him and beats him
pushes the ball away from him and with the turn straight to cover
full and angling in, driven down firmly and it hits the stumps
full and wide outside off, steered to deep point for one
angles it in towards middle stump, clipped nicely but straight to midwicket
shorter ball on the stumps and it's steered behind square on leg for one
too wide outside the off stump, called a wide
it's another direct hit, third umpire again! Williams steered the low full toss towards point and called for one quickly, Guptill hit the stumps at the bowler's end bu Williams had made it by then
short ball, smacked with a pull towards deep midwicket in the gap for two
flighted on lg, it's reverse-swept to deep point for two useful runs
comes down and drives the full toss straight to cover
loud cheers for the single as Williams goes back to whip the short of length ball towards square leg
sweeps the ball from way outside off and against the turn to square leg for one
comes down the track, Sodhi pitches it flat and short and Williams manages some bat with an edge, luckily just over Sodhi for one
short and slow on middle, semi-slapped towards deep midwicket for one
back of length outside off, smacked through the covers for one
wide full toss outside off, driven late and towards third man for one
back of length outside off, punched to cover off the back foot
drills the full delivery down the ground and Mitch stops it to save some runs
bangs in the short ball with the angle, Cremer pulls but is early into the shot and takes it on the body
beaten by the slower ball outside off, he pokes and misses
turns it away from outside off, he pushes at it and misses
comes down the ground to make it a full toss and lofts it down, right in the gap between long on and long off for four
reverse-sweeps the length delivery from leg stump to deep backward point for one more
bit of flight on of and he slog-sweeps that against the turn to deep midwicket
pushes that delivery down the ground and in the gap for two
some flight on the stumps, it's a full toss and driven down to long-on now
turning away from outside off, swishes at it away from the body
outside off and turning in, cut off the back foot behind square
pushes the length delivery into the covers with the turn and it's a fifty for Williams
works the ball with the turn towards deep midwicket and they manage to come back for the second
comes down the track and chips the ball down to long-off for one
bangs in the short ball, it's pulled off the middle to deep midwicket
short of length with room outside off, swatted back but mistimed by Cremer
cuts the short ball nicely this time towards deep backward point

that's a suicidal run out, that too after a full toss was pushed straight back to the bowler! The full toss was on the stumps, not smashed away but down the ground and Wheeler turned around quickly after stopping it to rattle the stumps at the non-striker's end because Cremer had walked a few yards by then
makes a lot of room, Wheeler's short ball chases him and Williams pulls it to deep square leg
short ball well outside off, it was slow too and Madziva chases and misses
starts off with a wide well outside off
what an elegant straight drive! It was pitched up, Williams made some room and lofted it straight down the ground to just beat long-on
it's gone only to cover and they take two! Full toss outside off was smashed to cover, the collection was not clean along with the drive and they took two
dropped by Neesham as Williams smashed it back to him, was around waist height but didn't stick in Neesham's hands
tries to reverse swat the ball from outside off behind square but misses
he gets it in that region but with a thick edge off a big drive and the ball flies over short third man for four!

another one held in the deep, big wicket of Williams this time! He slogged that length delivery on the leg side, it wasn't quite that full and Guptill came in a few yards to catch that comfortably. Williams looks at the toe end of his bat while walking back
chases the short of length ball outside off and gets a bottom edge
it's still alive, is it? Short ball closer to the batsman is dispatched to the midwicket boundary with a powerful hit for six
another bottom edge from well outside off goes to the keeper
this one moves away from the batsman as he chases while coming down the ground, called a wide
full toss just outside off, pushed into the covers and the fielder dives to save a run, or a few
another full toss outside off, it's steered straight to point
almost in the block hole outside off, driven into the covers for one now
it's full, it's straight and the middle stump is uprooted! Panyangara went too far and across to glance the ball to leg but missed it completely and the ball took out only one stump
full on the stumps again, pushed down the ground to long-on for one
low full toss on the stumps and it's driven into the covers, in the air, in the gap and they manage to come back for the second

that's it, last wicket falls and NZ take the series! Madziva was not in great position to pull that short ball and got a leading edge high on the leg side. Neesham at fine leg got under it nicely to take it in the deep
